Why I don't use Processing to do computer science education?
- Processing is a professional tool and is more complex and general than is needed in education. (Processing has a lot of APIs, which is hard to memorize and get started with)

Block-based programming VS Text-based programming
pros: 
- natural language description of blocks
- the drag-and-drop composition interaction

cons:
- lack of authenticity
- less powerful
